This program calculates the sum of all elements in an array. It uses a for...of loop to access each array element. Every value is added to a running total. After processing all elements, the final sum is displayed. This program introduces array traversal in JavaScript.
[ Javascript Practice Test ]
let numbers = [10, 20, 30, 40];
let total = 0;for (let num of numbers) {
total += num;
}
console.log("Sum =", total);
Output :
Sum = 100
